### ðŸŸ¡ Suggestion: Insufficient Signature Information
**Location**: [packages/core/src/tools/ast-edit.ts](file:///Users/caishanghong/Shopify/cli-tool/llxprt-code-2/packages/core/src/tools/ast-edit.ts) (Lines 322-335, 1630)
**Issue**: The current "Skeleton View" only provides the **name** and **type** (e.g., `function: myFunc`). It does **not** provide the parameters or return type, which dramatically reduces the utility of the context for the agent. The regex-based [extractFunctions](file:///Users/caishanghong/Shopify/cli-tool/llxprt-code-2/packages/core/src/tools/ast-edit.ts#1076-1115) (Lines 1076+) captures this, but the primary [ASTQueryExtractor](file:///Users/caishanghong/Shopify/cli-tool/llxprt-code-2/packages/core/src/tools/ast-edit.ts#222-375) (using ast-grep) does not seem to populate a "signature" field in [EnhancedDeclaration](file:///Users/caishanghong/Shopify/cli-tool/llxprt-code-2/packages/core/src/tools/ast-edit.ts#152-160).
**Suggestion**: Update [EnhancedDeclaration](file:///Users/caishanghong/Shopify/cli-tool/llxprt-code-2/packages/core/src/tools/ast-edit.ts#152-160) to include a `signature` field (e.g., [(a: string): void](file:///Users/caishanghong/Shopify/cli-tool/llxprt-code-2/packages/core/src/tools/ast-edit.ts#90-95)) and populate it in [ASTQueryExtractor](file:///Users/caishanghong/Shopify/cli-tool/llxprt-code-2/packages/core/src/tools/ast-edit.ts#222-375).

### ðŸŸ¡ Suggestion: Git Command Robustness
**Location**: [packages/core/src/tools/ast-edit.ts](file:///Users/caishanghong/Shopify/cli-tool/llxprt-code-2/packages/core/src/tools/ast-edit.ts) (Lines 445-451)
**Issue**: The `spawnSync` calls for git commands assume standard output format. While `encoding: 'utf-8'` is set, relying on string splitting by newline without handling potential filename encoding issues (e.g., spaces or non-ASCII chars in filenames, though rare in codebases) could be brittle.
**Suggestion**: Use `-z` (null terminator) for git commands (e.g., `git diff --name-only -z`) and split by `\0` for robustness.
